data.enText: to continue to live or exist

data.chText: 她是这家人中仅存的一员。
data.enText: She was the last surviving member of the family.

data.chText: 因这次撞车事故受伤的六人中，只有两人活了下来。
data.enText: Of the six people injured in the crash, only two survived.

data.chText: 有些奇怪的风俗是从早年留存下来的。
data.enText: Some strange customs have survived from earlier times.

data.chText: 一星期40英镑，我无法维持生活。
data.enText: I can't survive on £40 a week (= it is not enough for my basic needs) .

data.chText: 直至第二次参选失败他才不再担任党的领导人。
data.enText: He survived as party leader until his second election defeat.

data.chText: 别担心，只不过是划伤，你没事的。
data.enText: Don't worry, it's only a scratch─you'll survive.

data.chText: 幸存；幸免于难；艰难度过
data.enText: to continue to live or exist despite a dangerous event or time
The company managed to survive the crisis.
Many birds didn't survive the severe winter.

data.chText: 战争之后没几座完好的建筑了。
data.enText: Few buildings survived the war intact.
to live or exist longer than sb/sth

data.chText: 丈夫死后她又活了十年。
data.enText: She survived her husband by ten years.

simple_means.memory_skill: sur 上 + viv 生命 + e → 活在死亡之上 → 幸存

example: he could barely exist on such a low wage
Can you live on $2000 a month in New York City?
Many people in the world have to subsist on $1 a day

tr: continue to live through hardship or adversity
example: We went without water and food for 3 days
These superstitions survive in the backwaters of America
The race car driver lived through several very serious accidents
how long can a person last without food and water?
She outlived her husband by many years

tr: continue in existence after (an adversity, etc.)
example: He survived the cancer against all odds

value.def: If a person or living thing survives in a dangerous situation such as an accident or an illness, they do not die.

example.ex: ...the sequence of events that left the eight pupils battling to survive in icy seas for over four hours...
example.tran: 致使这 8 个小学生在冰冷的海水里挣扎求生四个多小时的一连串事件

example.ex: Those organisms that are most suited to the environment will be those that will survive...
example.tran: 最适宜该环境的微生物将会存活下来。

example.ex: Drugs that dissolve blood clots can help people survive heart attacks.
example.tran: 能溶解血栓的药物会有助于治疗心脏病。

value.def: If you survive in difficult circumstances, you manage to live or continue in spite of them and do not let them affect you very much.

example.ex: On my first day here I thought, 'Ooh, how will I survive?'
example.tran: 我第一天到这儿时就想，“天哪，我怎么能挺过去呢?”

example.ex: ...people who are struggling to survive without jobs...
Where once she had been totally self-sufficient, she now had to survive on income support.
example.tran: 她曾经完全能自给自足，而现在却不得不靠收入补助金维持生计。

example.ex: ...a man who had survived his share of boardroom coups.
example.tran: 董事会改组后仍然持有股份的人

value.def: If something survives, it continues to exist even after being in a dangerous situation or existing for a long time.

example.ex: When the market economy is introduced, many factories will not survive...
example.tran: 引入市场经济后，许多工厂将面临倒闭。

example.ex: The chances of a planet surviving a supernova always looked terribly slim.
example.tran: 行星躲过超新星爆发的几率总是十分渺茫。

example.ex: ...surviving examples of 19th-century architecture in the MidWest.
example.tran: 美国中西部几处仍留存至今的19世纪建筑

value.def: If you survive someone, you continue to live after they have died.

example.ex: Most women will survive their spouses...
example.tran: 大多数女性都比配偶长寿。

example.ex: She is survived by two daughters from her first marriage.
example.tran: 她身后留下了头婚时生的两个女儿。
威廉·莎士比亚最后一个健在的子孙

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 加强 + viv 生命 + ial 具有…的 → 生机勃勃 → 欢乐的
in 使… + vigor 精力 + ate 使… → 使有生命 → 鼓励
re 重新 + vital 有活力的；重要的 + ize 使… → 重新获得新生 → 恢复生气
re 重新 + viv 生命 + al 表行为 → 复活
re 重新 + viv 生命 + e → 重新活 → 复活
sur 上 + viv 生命 + al 表行为 → 存活下来
sur 上 + viv 生命 + e → 活在死亡之上 → 幸存
vi〔= viv〕生命 + able 能…的 → 能活的
vigil〔= vig〕生命 + ant …的 →〔动物〕保持警惕才能有生命 → 警惕的
vig 生命 + or 表状态 → 精力
vigor 精力 + ous …的 → 精力旺盛的
vit 生命 + al …的 → 有生命的 → 有活力的；重要的
vital 有活力的；重要的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 活力
vital 有活力的；重要的 + ize 使 → 赋予生命

partsOfSpeech.d: 重要器官；核心（有活力的东西）

partsOfSpeech.dec: vit 生命 + am 获得 + in …素 → 生命要素 → 维生素
viv 生命 + acious 多…的 → 多生命的 → 活泼的；有生气的
viv 生命 + id …的 → 生动的
viv 生命 + ify 使… → 使具有生气
vivi 生命 + sect 切割 → 活着切割 → 活体解剖
